TEXT.Text:
{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
To enter Sagittarius, a{C=0xFF016295/}Trophy of Victory{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is required. Since Crete has some of those, you can get one from her. Talk to Crete.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Restoration of Ophiuchus

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Ophiuchus has been corrupted by Serpens. As a result, the stars are becoming misaligned. Travel to Ophiuchus and defeat Serpens.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Serpens

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Serpens is constantly hunting {C=0xFFFF0000/}Pheos{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Defeat Serpens so he may never tempt {C=0xFFFF0000/}Pheos{C=0xFF4D0D08/} again.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' Recovery

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Crete tells us {C=0xFFFF0000/}Pheos{C=0xFF4D0D08/} has disappeared again. It appears he has once again gone off to Ophiuchus for his research. Travel to Ophiuchus and find {C=0xFFFF0000/}Pheos{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Restoration of Ophiuchus

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The patterns of the stars are starting to misalign once more. Something must have happened in Ophiuchus again. Travel to Ophiuchus and defeat Serpens to restore things to Normal.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Serpens

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The same Serpens that tempted {C=0xFFFF0000/}Pheos{C=0xFF4D0D08/} before has reappeared. He may try to tempt {C=0xFFFF0000/}Pheos{C=0xFF4D0D08/} once again. Go to Ophiuchus and defeat Serpens.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' Recovery

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFFFF0000/}Pheos{C=0xFF4D0D08/} has disappeared. He must have gone back to Ophiuchus in the hopes of curing Crete. Travel to Ophiuchus and look for {C=0xFFFF0000/}Pheos{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Hydra

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Its power and confidence seems to be related to its three heads. Gather a party and defeat the three headed {C=0xFFFF0000/}Hydra{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Hydra

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The three headed sea beast {C=0xFFFF0000/}Hydra{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. It may have three heads, but they say only one of them is real. Defeat the real head and save Ophiuchus.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Hydra

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
A monster with not one, not two, but three heads has appeared in Ophiuchus. People are terrified to even go near it. Go to Ophiuchus and defeat the monster.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Kingspion

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Perseus' wife has such horrible cooking skills, that her food induces food poisoning. To appreciate his loving wife's cooking, Perseus always needs a little antidote on the side. Defeat Kingspion and retrieve the antidote for Perseus.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Kingspion

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kingspion's poison is also used as an antidote. Perseus needs Kingspion poison to treat his wife who has fallen ill. Help Perseus and defeat Kingspion.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Kingspion

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kingspion has returned to Scorpio. The poisonous mist he spreads is making travelers to Scorpio sick. Defeat Kingspion to get rid of the poisonous mist.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Rescue Persephone

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Hades has taken Persephone captive again. Her beauty has him completely enthralled and he is relentless in tormenting her. Defeat Hades and save Persephone.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Resuce Persephone

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Hades is a well-known skirt chaser, and he is constantly troubling Persephone. Help poor Persephone and defeat Hades.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Rescue Persephone

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Something awful may have happened in Virgo. Someone seems to be chasing Persephone the last time Crete heard from her. go to Virgo and find out if Persephone is well and unharmed.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Kyrab

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Heracles has gone alone to hunt for the delicacy of the Galaxy, {C=0xFFFF0000/}Kyrab{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. He was almost hunted himself. Travel with Heracles to Cancer and defeat {C=0xFFFF0000/}Kyrab{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Kyrab

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Heracles always brings back crabs for dinner. Hunt for {C=0xFFFF0000/}Kyrab{C=0xFF4D0D08/} with Heracles.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Kyrab

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFFFF0000/}Kyrab{C=0xFF4D0D08/} has reappeared. go with Heracles and help defeat {C=0xFFFF0000/}Kyrab{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Minotaur

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Europa{C=0xFF4D0D08/}'s forgetfulness might be a bigger problem than the {C=0xFFFF0000/}Minotaur{C=0xFF4D0D08/} himself. Trying to solve the issue through conversation might further endanger Taurus. Stop the {C=0xFFFF0000/}Minotaur{C=0xFF4D0D08/}'s rampage.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Minotaur

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Europa{C=0xFF4D0D08/} has no intention of putting an end to the{C=0xFFFF0000/}Minotaur{C=0xFF4D0D08/}'s violence. Travel to Taurus and stop {C=0xFFFF0000/}Minotaur{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Minotaur

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
For some reason, the {C=0xFFFF0000/}Minotaur{C=0xFF4D0D08/} of Taurus is on a rampage. Meet with {C=0xFF00863C/}Europa{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and ask her to calm the {C=0xFFFF0000/}Minotaur{C=0xFF4D0D08/} down.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Black Dragon Lord's Essence (Wing)
Ophiuchus Star Fragment

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Combine the Black Dragon Lord's Essence (Wing) and the Ophiuchus Star Fragment to create the Galaxy Guardian Cloak.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
[Hero] Wing of Black Dragon Lord

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
If you bring the Wing of Black Dragon Lord, his essence can be extracted From it.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
[Hero] Shoes of Black Dragon Lord

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bring the Shoes of Black Dragon Lord as proof of his defeat, and Crete will reward you with {C=0xFFFF0000/}Black Dragon Lord's Essence (Shoes){C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
[Hero] Gloves of Black Dragon Lord

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bring Gloves of Black Dragon Lord as proof of his defeat, and Crete will reward you with {C=0xFFFF0000/}Black Dragon Lord's Essence (Gloves){C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
[Hero] Shoulderguard of Black Dragon Lord

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bring Shoulderguard of Black Dragon Lord as proof of his defeat, and Crete will reward you with {C=0xFFFF0000/}Black Dragon Lord's Essence (Shoulder){C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
[Hero] Bottom of Black Dragon Lord

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bring Bottom of Black Dragon Lord as proof of his defeat, and Crete will reward you with {C=0xFFFF0000/}Black Dragon Lord's Essence (Bottom){C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
[Hero] Top of Black Dragon Lord

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bring Top of Black Dragon Lord as proof of his defeat, and Crete will reward you with {C=0xFFFF0000/}Black Dragon Lord's Essence (Top){C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
[Hero] Helmet of Black Dragon Lord

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bring Helmet of Black Dragon Lord as proof of his defeat, and Crete will reward you with {C=0xFFFF0000/}Black Dragon Lord's Essence (Helm){C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
[Hero] Weapon of Black Dragon Lord

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bring Weapon of Black Dragon Lord as proof of his defeat, and Crete will reward you with {C=0xFFFF0000/}Black Dragon Lord's Essence (Weapon){C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to the Villagers
(Must be in the correct order)

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[[Quest NPC]]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Winds - Steven the 2nd

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Prosperity has returned to the kingdom. Not long ago it was facing a financial crisis, but now the port is busy and the streets bustle with activity. Speak with the merchants in town to find out what happened.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Constellation Ring

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[[Quest NPC]]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
To gain access to {C=0xFFFF0000/}Ophiuchus{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, a {C=0xFF016295/}Constellation Ring{C=0xFF4D0D08/} needs to be created by combining the 5 Keys. Speak with Crete to create the {C=0xFF016295/}Constellation Ring{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Speak with Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
To reward the heroes who have saved {C=0xFF00863C/}Pheos{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and brought peace to the Galaxy, Crete has found a way to gather the hidden strength of the stars to create Protector of Stars Equipment.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' Recovery

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[[Quest NPC]]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The 5 Keys to {C=0xFFFF0000/}Ophiuchus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} have been collected. On Saturdays and Sundays, when {C=0xFFFF0000/}Ophiuchus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} opens, travel there to find the whereabouts of {C=0xFF00863C/}Pheos,{C=0xFF4D0D08/} the lover of Crete and the master of the Stars.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to the NPCs in town (must be in sequence)

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Steven Jr.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Steven Jr. is worrying that tax revenues are getting less and less. He has heard that harvest is also failing. Investigate this matter by {C=0xFF7D0000/}talking with the NPCs in town.{C=0xFF4D0D08/}

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Investigate the area where the meteorr hit
( After investigation, remote quest completion is possible )

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Colin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Guard Captain Colin is really concerned with the news that a {C=0xFF7D0000/}meteorr fell into the village{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. He's worred it may become a threat to Kingdom. Since it could also be a danger to Dragotaka, it may be best if you go and investigate yourself.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pios' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Crete asks to find her fiancé, {C=0xFF00863C/}Pios, the owner of 10 constellations{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. She said he was trapped in {C=0xFF016295/}Ophiuchus Dungeon{C=0xFF4D0D08/} after he met the {C=0xFFFF0000/}mysterious snake{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and started practicingmedicine with him. Let's ask Crete what happened to him.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pios' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
To enter the Ophiuchus Dungeon, {C=0xFF016295/}a Constellation Ring{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is needed, you can create one by combining 5 keys from the other Dungeons. Since each Dungeon is related to a day of the week, there are time restrictions on entrance. To enter Ophiuchus, gather your keys during the week and try to find Pios on Saturday and Sunday. ({C=0xFF016295/}Constellation Ring{C=0xFF4D0D08/}can be obtained from Crete's menu :{C=0xFFFF0000/}Blend{C=0xFF4D0D08/})

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain the Golden Fleece from Aries

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pios' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Of the 5 keys needed, the Moonlit Key must be obtained first. It can be obtained from {C=0xFF00863C/}Europa{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in the Taurus Dungeon which is available on Monday. However, to enter the Taurus Dungeon, a{C=0xFF00863C/}Golden Fleece{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is required. If you go to {C=0xFFFF0000/}Aries, there you will encounter the Golden Ram{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, so go to the Aries Dungeon to get a Golden Fleece.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Meet Europa in Taurus Dungeon 

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pios' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Europa{C=0xFF4D0D08/} doesn't want anyone to be near her, because she's tired of {C=0xFF7D0000/}Hades{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and his constant proposals.  Explain the situation to {C=0xFF00863C/}Europa{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and obtain the{C=0xFF016295/}Moonlit Key{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Be careful with {C=0xFFFF0000/}The Minotaur{C=0xFF4D0D08/} though, he can be a little overprotective.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Ask the Twins for help in Gemini Dungeon 

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pios' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The {C=0xFF016295/}Comet Key{C=0xFF4D0D08/} can be obtained from the monster crab, Keyrab, in Cancer. However, it's hard to approach Cancer since everything went wrong. 
 {C=0xFF00863C/}The Twins{C=0xFF4D0D08/}might be able to help you with this. Go to {C=0xFFFF0000/}Gemini which opens on Tuesday{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and ask for help. However, be careful; they may also have been effected by the Chaos.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain the Comet Key from Cancer

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pios' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The{C=0xFF016295/}Comet Key{C=0xFF4D0D08/} can be obtained from the{C=0xFFFF0000/}Monster Crab, Kyrab{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in Cancer. If you have the{C=0xFF016295/}Leading Compass{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from Gemini, you have no problem in entering Cancer. After you defeat Kyrab, you will receive the {C=0xFF016295/}Comet Key{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, the second key.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain Unicorn's Horn from Leo Dungeon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pios' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The third key, {C=0xFF016295/}Blue Star Key{C=0xFF4D0D08/} can be obtained in {C=0xFFFF0000/}Virgo which is opened on Wednesday{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. However, since it's protected by the Seal, it's hard to enter. To break the Seal, the Symbol of Purity, the{C=0xFF016295/}Unicorn's Horn{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is needed. This can be found in the Leo Dungeon, which is open on Wednesday, defeat the {C=0xFFFF0000/}Monster Lion Cleonae{C=0xFF4D0D08/}which protects the {C=0xFF016295/}Unicorn's Horn{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and get the item you need.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Ask Persephone for help in the Dungeon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pios' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
If you have {C=0xFF016295/}Unicorn's Horn{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, you can break through the seal into Virgo. Please go to {C=0xFFFF0000/}Virgo which opens on Wednesday{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and talk to Persephone to get {C=0xFF016295/}Blue Star Key{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain Feather of Pegasus from Pegasus Dungeon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pios' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
It's able to get the fourth key, called the {C=0xFF016295/}Green Star Key{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, from Knigspion in Scorpio. However, the passage to get to the place is filled with poison and you cannot walk through. If you have a Flying Horse Pegasus, it would be possible to get there. Go to {C=0xFFFF0000/}Pegasus which opens on Thursday{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and ask Pegasus for help.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain Green Star Key from Scorpio Dungeon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pios' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
If you have {C=0xFF016295/}Feather of Pegasus{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, you can avoid the poison and enter {C=0xFFFF0000/}Scorpio which is opened on Thursday{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Now defeat{C=0xFFFF0000/} Kingspion{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and get the{C=0xFF016295/}Green Star Key{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Ask Chiron for help from Sagittarius Dungeon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pios' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
We have only one key left to get. The last key is possessed by {C=0xFFFF0000/}The Hydra{C=0xFF4D0D08/} which has many heads. To wake up the sleeping Hydra,you will need the {C=0xFF016295/}Harp of the Goddess{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, which you can get from Wise Chiron. Go to Sagittarius which opens on Friday and talk to Chiron to get the {C=0xFF016295/}Harp of the Goddess{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain the Gold Star Key from Hydra Dungeon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[[Quest NPC]]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pheos' lover - Crete

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Details]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The fifth key, {C=0xFF016295/}Gold Star Key{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is obtainable from the {C=0xFFFF0000/}Hydra Dungeon which is available on Friday{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. The{C=0xFFFF0000/} Hydra{C=0xFF4D0D08/} needs to be killed. You should use {C=0xFF016295/}Harp of the Goddess{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to wake up the monster and get the {C=0xFF016295/}Gold Star Key{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Crete

